SIMPLE: invitation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Invitation
<hw>In`vi*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>invitatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>invitation</ets>. See
<er>Invite</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of inviting; solicitation; the requesting of
a person's company; <as>as, an <ex>invitation</ex> to a party, to a
dinner, or to visit a friend</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A document written or printed, or spoken words,
conveying the message by which one is invited.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Allurement; enticement.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She gives the leer of <qex>invitation</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>invitational</ent>⟦br⟧
